    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Ooh! I will try a Gordon&#8217;s Cup &#8211; I am currently obsessed with refreshing citrusy beverages that aren&#8217;t too sweet. And I am always searching for the perfect one when out for a drink but they come close but no cigar for one reason or another. The Orbit Room on Market St. in SF (for any Bay Area people, or when you visit, Molly) is a great place to get a freshly muddled cocktail. They have an awesome drink with fresh cilantro muddled with ginger, lime and tequila. Light and great. I also had a great drink with campari and whisky (don&#8217;t be scared- I know lotsa people hate Campari!), fresh grapefruit and bergamot syrup. It wasn&#8217;t bitter at all.</p>
    </div>

